------------
NPN surfaces
------------

NPN surface stands for Not (Positive & Negative) surface.
NPN surfaces are declared as

    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 _:bng_2 int).

    _:bng_1 {
        triples
    }

    _:bng_2 {
        triples
    }

This is equivalent with the classical logical implication

    _:bng_1 => _:bng_2.

with explicit scoping via graffiti and using RDF TriG syntax.

Declaring a positive surface:

    (graffiti) log:npn (true _:bng_2 1).

Declaring a negative surface:

    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 false 1).

Declaring a query:

    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 _:bng_2 0).

Declaring a component (conclusion triple of a backwardf rule):

    (graffiti) log:npn (_:bng_1 _:bng_2 -1).
